Body almost entirely covered by plates except for region overlying opening of swim bladder capsule, area between pectoral girdle and lower lip, region around anus, and area around base of paired fins. Rostral plate with posterior notch articulation of mesethmoid. Rostral plate thickened, with odontode-free area between dorsad and ventrad series of odontodes ( Fig. 41 ). Snout plates anterior to nares reduced, small unplated area at lateral portion between rostral plate and nostril. Three rows of predorsal plates. Lateral line incomplete, with gap without pores along middle length of body. Median plate series truncated, not reaching posterior end of caudal peduncle (
Fig. 4g
). Abdominal plates arranged in three rows anteriorly and irregularly arranged between pelvic-fin insertions. Lateral abdominal plates slightly larger and forming regular series. Median abdominal series formed by one or two plate series, pre-anal shield region formed by median to large plates (
Fig. 8g
). Coracoid and cleithrum exposed and covered by odontodes, except for median region of cleithrum between arrector fossae openings and medial region of coracoids.
